text.section:
Each board of education shall file in the board's office its policies relating to the following matters:
Transportation of pupils;
Discipline and conduct of pupils;
Limitations or restrictions on use of school facilities;
Conduct of meetings of the board of education, including policies on the calling of executive sessions;
Personnel policies that apply to certified employees, including fringe benefits, salary schedules, nonclassroom duties, in-service training, teacher-student ratio, hiring, assignment, transfer, dismissal, suspension, reinstatement, promotion, and demotion;
Evaluation of certified employees;
Selection of textbooks and instructional materials;
Expenditure and accounting for school funds, including all special funds; and
Policies dealing with school-based decision making.
